hh3cNqa.name: hh3cNqa
hh3cNqa.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cNqa.description: The private MIB file includes the test information of the device. It is supplementary for rfc2925.txt.

hh3cNqaUdpEcho.name: hh3cNqaUdpEcho
hh3cNqaUdpEcho.description: Indicates that an implementation is using the UDP based echo server. Notes: The hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort and hh3cNqaCtlSourcePort need to be set, while in the pingUdpEcho Node, hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort must be set to the default value.

hh3cNqaTcpconnect.name: hh3cNqaTcpconnect
hh3cNqaTcpconnect.description: Indicates that an implementation is attempting to connect to a TCP port in order to calculate a round trip time. Notes: The hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort and hh3cNqaCtlSourcePort need to be set, while in the pingTcpConnectionAttempt Node, hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort must be set to the default value.

hh3cNqajitter.name: hh3cNqajitter
hh3cNqajitter.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for packet transfers. 'jitter' will cause the NQA(Network Quality Analysis) application to perform delay variance analysis.

hh3cNqaHttp.name: hh3cNqaHttp
hh3cNqaHttp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for name resolution, tcp connect and tcp data transfer mechanisms for HTTP data download from a particular HTTP Server. It causes the NQA application to perform a download of the object specified in the URL.

hh3cNqadlsw.name: hh3cNqadlsw
hh3cNqadlsw.description: Indicates that an implementation is using tcp for sending keepalives. 'dlsw' will cause the NQA application to perform a keepalive operation to measure the response time of a DLSw peer.

hh3cNqadhcp.name: hh3cNqadhcp
hh3cNqadhcp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for sending dhcp requests. 'dhcp' will cause the NQA application to perform an IP Address lease request/teardown operation.

hh3cNqaftp.name: hh3cNqaftp
hh3cNqaftp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using tcp packet for ftp connect and data transfer.

hh3cNqaMIBVersion.name: hh3cNqaMIBVersion
hh3cNqaMIBVersion.description: Version string of this MIB. The format will be: 'Version.Release.Patch: Description' An instance likes: '1.0.0: Initial NQA MIB'

hh3cNqaCtlTable.name: hh3cNqaCtlTable
hh3cNqaCtlTable.description: Defines the NQA Control Extend Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing network analysis operations at a remote host.

hh3cNqaCtlEntry.name: hh3cNqaCtlEntry
hh3cNqaCtlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hh3cNqaCtlTable. The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort.name: hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort
hh3cNqaCtlTargetPort.description: The destination port that may be used by udpEcho, tcpConnect and jitter probes.

hh3cNqaCtlSourcePort.name: hh3cNqaCtlSourcePort
hh3cNqaCtlSourcePort.description: The source port that may be used by all tests except for dns and dlsw. If no source port is specified, system will create a random port as source port.

hh3cNqaCtlTTL.name: hh3cNqaCtlTTL
hh3cNqaCtlTTL.description: Specifies the value to store in the TTL Field in the IP packet used to encapsulate the NQA probe.

hh3cNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval.name: hh3cNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval
hh3cNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval.description: Time value in milliseconds that is an interval between two continuous probes in jitter test. This object is only used by jitter test.

hh3cNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets.name: hh3cNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets
hh3cNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets.description: Packet number that specifys how many packets will be sent in one jitter test. This object is only used by jitter test.

hh3cNqaCtlHttpOperationType.name: hh3cNqaCtlHttpOperationType
hh3cNqaCtlHttpOperationType.description: Http operation type: get or post.

hh3cNqaCtlHttpOperationString.name: hh3cNqaCtlHttpOperationString
hh3cNqaCtlHttpOperationString.description: Http operation string. For example, if the http operation type is get, the string will be url, home page and http version.

hh3cNqaCtlFtpOperationString.name: hh3cNqaCtlFtpOperationString
hh3cNqaCtlFtpOperationString.description: Ftp operation string. If the ftp operation type is get, the string must be the file name which will be gotten from ftp server.

hh3cNqaCtlVPNInstance.name: hh3cNqaCtlVPNInstance
hh3cNqaCtlVPNInstance.description: VPN name by which system finds route in the specified VPN to send NQA probe packets.

hh3cNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime.name: hh3cNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime
hh3cNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime.description: To indicate how long the history records will be saved in the pingProbeHistoryTable table after the test stopped.

hh3cNqaCtlHistoryEnable.name: hh3cNqaCtlHistoryEnable
hh3cNqaCtlHistoryEnable.description: To indicate whether the history should be recorded in the PingProbeHistoryTable or not. enabled(1) --history will be recorded disabled(2) --history will not be recorded.

hh3cNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor.name: hh3cNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor
hh3cNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor.description: The advantage factor depends on the type of access and how the service is to be used. This object will be used while calculating the ICPIF (Calculated Planning Impairment Factor) values. Suggestion values: |-----------------------------------|-------| | Service |factor | |-----------------------------------|-------| |conventional wire-line | 0 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |mobility within Building | 5 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |mobility within geographical area | 10 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |access to hard-to-reach location | 20 | |-----------------------------------|-------|

hh3cNqaCtlCodecType.name: hh3cNqaCtlCodecType
hh3cNqaCtlCodecType.description: To indicate the codec type to be used with jitter probe. This is applicable only for the jitter probe.

hh3cNqaResultsTable.name: hh3cNqaResultsTable
hh3cNqaResultsTable.description: Defines the NQA Results Extend Table for providing the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the hh3cNqaResultsTable. The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

hh3cNqaResultsEntry.name: hh3cNqaResultsEntry
hh3cNqaResultsEntry.description: The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

hh3cNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects
hh3cNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the destination became disconnected. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hh3cNqaResultsRttTimeouts.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttTimeouts
hh3cNqaResultsRttTimeouts.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe timed out.

hh3cNqaResultsRttBusies.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttBusies
hh3cNqaResultsRttBusies.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because all NQA tasks have been running. If a new probe fails to start, the value of this object is incremented. The next test will not start until the next Frequency.

hh3cNqaResultsRttNoConnections.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttNoConnections
hh3cNqaResultsRttNoConnections.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe destination is unavailable. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hh3cNqaResultsRttDrops.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttDrops
hh3cNqaResultsRttDrops.description: The number of times that a NQA operation failed to initiated for unavailibility of necessary internal resources.

hh3cNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors
hh3cNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors.description: The number of packets arrived out of sequence.

hh3cNqaResultsRttStatsErrors.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttStatsErrors
hh3cNqaResultsRttStatsErrors.description: The number of some other errors.

hh3cNqaResultsMaxDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaResultsMaxDelaySD
hh3cNqaResultsMaxDelaySD.description: The maximal delay from source device to destination device. Currently this value is only used for jitter test, and this value must be 0 in other type test. In jitter test, if destination system time is not valid, the SD delay may be set 0.

hh3cNqaResultsMaxDelayDS.name: hh3cNqaResultsMaxDelayDS
hh3cNqaResultsMaxDelayDS.description: The maximal delay from destination device to source device. Currently this value is only used for jitter test, and this value is 0 in other type test. In jitter test, if destination system time is not valid, the DS delay may be set 0.

hh3cNqaResultsLostPacketRatio.name: hh3cNqaResultsLostPacketRatio
hh3cNqaResultsLostPacketRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the drop rate of NQA test. For example, this value is 30 that means source device only had received 70% packets of total sent packets.

hh3cNqaResultsPacketLateArrival.name: hh3cNqaResultsPacketLateArrival
hh3cNqaResultsPacketLateArrival.description: The value of this object indicates the number of the packets that arrived after the timeout.

hh3cNqaResultsRttSum.name: hh3cNqaResultsRttSum
hh3cNqaResultsRttSum.description: The sum of round trip time.

hh3cNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD
hh3cNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD.description: The number of delay from source to destination that are successfully measured.

hh3cNqaResultsMinDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaResultsMinDelaySD
hh3cNqaResultsMinDelaySD.description: The minimum of all one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaResultsSumDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaResultsSumDelaySD
hh3cNqaResultsSumDelaySD.description: The sum of one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaResultsSum2DelaySD.name: hh3cNqaResultsSum2DelaySD
hh3cNqaResultsSum2DelaySD.description: The sum of squares of one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS.name: hh3cNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS
hh3cNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS.description: The number of delay from destination to source that are successfully measured.

hh3cNqaResultsMinDelayDS.name: hh3cNqaResultsMinDelayDS
hh3cNqaResultsMinDelayDS.description: The minimum of all one way times from destination to source.

hh3cNqaResultsSumDelayDS.name: hh3cNqaResultsSumDelayDS
hh3cNqaResultsSumDelayDS.description: The sum of one way times from destination to source.

hh3cNqaResultsSum2DelayDS.name: hh3cNqaResultsSum2DelayDS
hh3cNqaResultsSum2DelayDS.description: The sum of squares of one way times from destination to source.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsTable.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsTable
hh3cNqaJitterStatsTable.description: Statistics table for latest jitter activity.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsEntry.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsEntry
hh3cNqaJitterStatsEntry.description: An entry contains the statistics for the latest jitter activity. This entry is created only if the pingCtlType is hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT
hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.description: The number of received destination device responses with which jitter test can reach round-trip time.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD.description: The number that records positive jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of the value of all positive jitters in packets sent from source to destination.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD.description: The number that records negative jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of all negative jitter values in packets sent from source to destination.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of the value of all negative jitters in packets sent from source to destination.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS.description: The number that records positive jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS.description: The number that records negative jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD.description: The lost packets number sent from source to destination.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS.description: The lost packets number sent from destination to source.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from source to destination.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD
hh3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from source to destination.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from destination to source.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from destination to source.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown
hh3cNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown.description: The number of packets which is lost with unknown reason.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF
hh3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF.description: The ICPIF (Calculated Planning Impairment Factor) value for the latest jitter test.

hh3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS.name: hh3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS
hh3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS.description: The MOS (Mean Opinion Score) value for the latest jitter test.

hh3cNqaTcpServerTable.name: hh3cNqaTcpServerTable
hh3cNqaTcpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of NQA tcp server configuration information.

hh3cNqaTcpServerEntry.name: hh3cNqaTcpServerEntry
hh3cNqaTcpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of NQA tcp server configuration information. This entry includes not only the tcp server ip address but also the tcp server port.

hh3cNqaTcpServerRowStatus.name: hh3cNqaTcpServerRowStatus
hh3cNqaTcpServerRowStatus.description: hh3cNqaTcpServerIpAddress and hh3cNqaTcpServerPort must be set during a creation operation.

hh3cNqaUdpServerTable.name: hh3cNqaUdpServerTable
hh3cNqaUdpServerTable.description: Status of NQA udp server configuration information.

hh3cNqaUdpServerEntry.name: hh3cNqaUdpServerEntry
hh3cNqaUdpServerEntry.description: This entry includes not only the udp server ip address but also the udp server udp port.

hh3cNqaUdpServerRowStatus.name: hh3cNqaUdpServerRowStatus
hh3cNqaUdpServerRowStatus.description: hh3cNqaUdpServerIpAddress and hh3cNqaUdpServerPort must be set during a creation operation.

hh3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.name: hh3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber
hh3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.description: The maximum number saved per group. The maximum value of hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber can not exceed the value of this object.

hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable.name: hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable
hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable.description: Defines the NQA statistics control table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable and the hh3cNqaGroupStatsJitterTable.

hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlEntry.name: hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlEntry
hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable. The hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable has the same index as the pingCtlTable in order for a hh3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable to correspond to the pingCtlEntry.

hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.name: hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval
hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.description: Statistic information will be calculated after the time that is the value of hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.

hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber.name: hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber
hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber.description: The value of this object indicates the number of group saved. The length of this object is from 1 to hh3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.

hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime.name: hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime
hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime.description: To indicate how long the statistic information will be saved after the test stops.

hh3cNqaCtlBeginTime.name: hh3cNqaCtlBeginTime
hh3cNqaCtlBeginTime.description: Time at which the type-specified test will start.

hh3cNqaCtlLifeTime.name: hh3cNqaCtlLifeTime
hh3cNqaCtlLifeTime.description: To indicate how long the type-specified test will last.

hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable.name: hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable
hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable.description: Defines the NQA statistics results table for providing the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The statistics results of these operations in a statistic cycle are stored in the hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The statistic cycle is the value of hh3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval. The first two index identify the pingCtlEntry that the probe statistics result (Hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry) belongs to.

hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry.name: hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry
hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable has the same index as the pingCtlTable in order for a hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry to correspond to the pingCtlEntry that caused it to be created.

hh3cNqaStatResIndex.name: hh3cNqaStatResIndex
hh3cNqaStatResIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the statistics result of a NQA probe is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning hh3cNqaStatResIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType.name: hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType
hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of address stored in the corresponding hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress object.

hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress.name: hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress
hh3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress.description: This object represent the host address to be used at a remote host for performing a network analysis operation.

hh3cNqaStatResMinRtt.name: hh3cNqaStatResMinRtt
hh3cNqaStatResMinRtt.description: The minimum NQA probe round-trip-time (RTT) received. The value of 0 for this object implies that no RTT has been received.

hh3cNqaStatResMaxRtt.name: hh3cNqaStatResMaxRtt
hh3cNqaStatResMaxRtt.description: The maximum NQA probe round-trip-time (RTT) received. The value of 0 for this object implies that no RTT has been received.

hh3cNqaStatResProbeResponses.name: hh3cNqaStatResProbeResponses
hh3cNqaStatResProbeResponses.description: The number of responses received. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.

hh3cNqaStatResSentProbes.name: hh3cNqaStatResSentProbes
hh3cNqaStatResSentProbes.description: The value of this object reflects the number of probes sent. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probes have been sent.

hh3cNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares
hh3cNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares.description: This object contains the sum of the squares for all NQA responses received. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no NQA responses have been received.

hh3cNqaStatResStartTime.name: hh3cNqaStatResStartTime
hh3cNqaStatResStartTime.description: This object contains the start time of the statistic.

hh3cNqaStatResInterval.name: hh3cNqaStatResInterval
hh3cNqaStatResInterval.description: This object contains the interval between two times of statistic.

hh3cNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects
hh3cNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the destination became disconnected. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hh3cNqaStatResRttTimeouts.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttTimeouts
hh3cNqaStatResRttTimeouts.description: The number of times that a probe failed because the probe timed out.

hh3cNqaStatResRttBusies.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttBusies
hh3cNqaStatResRttBusies.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because errors related to sockets.

hh3cNqaStatResRttNoConnections.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttNoConnections
hh3cNqaStatResRttNoConnections.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe destination is unavailable. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hh3cNqaStatResRttDrops.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttDrops
hh3cNqaStatResRttDrops.description: The number of times that a NQA operation failed to initiate for unavailibility of necessary internal resources.

hh3cNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors
hh3cNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors.description: The number of packets arrived out of sequence.

hh3cNqaStatResLostPacketRatio.name: hh3cNqaStatResLostPacketRatio
hh3cNqaStatResLostPacketRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the drop rate of NQA test packet. For example, if the value is 30, that means source device only had received 70 percent packets of total sent packets.

hh3cNqaStatResPacketLateArrival.name: hh3cNqaStatResPacketLateArrival
hh3cNqaStatResPacketLateArrival.description: The value of this object reflects the number of the packets that arrived after the timeout.

hh3cNqaStatResRttSum.name: hh3cNqaStatResRttSum
hh3cNqaStatResRttSum.description: This object contains the sum of the squares for all NQA responses received during the test lifetime. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no NQA responses have been received.

hh3cNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD
hh3cNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD.description: The number of one way times from source to destination that are successfully measured.

hh3cNqaStatResMinDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaStatResMinDelaySD
hh3cNqaStatResMinDelaySD.description: The minimum one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaStatResMaxDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaStatResMaxDelaySD
hh3cNqaStatResMaxDelaySD.description: The maximum one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaStatResSumDelaySD.name: hh3cNqaStatResSumDelaySD
hh3cNqaStatResSumDelaySD.description: The sum of one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaStatResSum2DelaySD.name: hh3cNqaStatResSum2DelaySD
hh3cNqaStatResSum2DelaySD.description: The sum of squares of one way times from source to destination.

hh3cNqaGroupStatsJitterEntry.name: hh3cNqaGroupStatsJitterEntry

hh3cNqaStatJitterIndex.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterIndex
hh3cNqaStatJitterIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the statistic result of a NQA probe in a statistic cycle is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning hh3cNqaStatJitterIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

hh3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosSD.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosSD

hh3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfPosDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosDS.description: The number that records positive jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaStatJitterSumOfPosDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hh3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegDS.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegDS

hh3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegDS.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegDS

hh3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegDS.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegDS

hh3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegDS.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegDS

hh3cNqaStatJitterMinOfICPIF.name: hh3cNqaStatJitterMinOfICPIF
hh3cNqaStatJitterMinOfICPIF.description: The minimum of all ICPIF values in a statistic cycle for jitter test.

hh3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfMOS.description: The maximum of all MOS values in a statistic cycle for jitter test.

hh3cNqaReactionTable.name: hh3cNqaReactionTable
hh3cNqaReactionTable.description: A table of NQA test monitoring notification and reaction configuration definitions. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding pingCtlEntry is deleted.

hh3cNqaReactionEntry.name: hh3cNqaReactionEntry
hh3cNqaReactionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hh3cNqaReactionTable. The first two index elements identify the pingCtlEntry that a hh3cNqaReactItemIndex belongs to. The third index element selects a single reaction.

hh3cNqaReactOwnerIndex.name: hh3cNqaReactOwnerIndex
hh3cNqaReactOwnerIndex.description: The first index of hh3cNqaReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlOwnerIndex in pingCtlTable. hh3cNqaReactOwnerIndex and hh3cNqaReactTestName identify an existed test.

hh3cNqaReactTestName.name: hh3cNqaReactTestName
hh3cNqaReactTestName.description: The second index of hh3cNqaReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlTestName in pingCtlTable. hh3cNqaReactOwnerIndex and hh3cNqaReactTestName identify an existed test.

hh3cNqaReactItemIndex.name: hh3cNqaReactItemIndex
hh3cNqaReactItemIndex.description: The third index of hh3cNqaReactionTable, it definitely identifies one of the reaction configurations for a test.

hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement.name: hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement
hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement.description: A list of reaction condition type. 'probetime' and 'probefailure' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is not hh3cNqajitter. 'jitterOwdSD': one way time from source to destination in jitter test. 'jitterOwdDS': one way time from destination to source in jitter test. 'jitterrtt', 'jitterpacketloss', 'jittersd', 'jitterds', 'jitterOwdSD' and 'jitterOwdDS' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter. 'icpif' and 'mos' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter and hh3cNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.

hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit.name: hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit
hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit.description: This object defines an administrative upper-threshold value for hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement. The value of this object is zero if hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement is specified as 'jitterpacketloss' and 'probefailure'.

hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit.name: hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit
hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit.description: This object defines an administrative lower-threshold value for hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement. The value of hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit should be equal or less than the value of hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. The value of this object is zero if hh3cNqaReactCheckedElement is specified as 'jitterpacketloss' and 'probefailure'.

hh3cNqaReactThresholdType.name: hh3cNqaReactThresholdType
hh3cNqaReactThresholdType.description: This object defines the reaction threshold types. invalid(0): Invalid value. average(1): If reaction threshold type is average and the average value of watched operation exceeds threshold limit, an action specified in hh3cNqaReactActionType is generated when hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. consecutive(2): If reaction threshold type is consecutive and the times of watched operation consecutively exceeds the limit specified by hh3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum, an action specified in hh3cNqaReactActionType is generated when hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. accumulative(3): If reaction threshold type is accumulative and the times of watched operation accumulatively exceeds the limit specified by hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum, an action specified in hh3cNqaReactActionType is generated when hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. If reaction threshold type is not configured, the value of this object is 'invalid'.

hh3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum.name: hh3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum
hh3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum.description: This object defines a consecutive threshold limit. The value is zero when hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is not 'consecutive'.

hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum.name: hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum
hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum.description: This object defines an accumulative threshold limit. The value is zero when the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is not 'accumulative'.

hh3cNqaReactActionType.name: hh3cNqaReactActionType
hh3cNqaReactActionType.description: Specifies the type of reaction to generate if the specified violation type occurs for the monitored element: none - No reaction is generated trapOnly - A trap is generated triggerOnly - All trigger actions defined for this entry are generated trapAndTrigger - Both a trap and all trigger actions are generated

hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus.name: hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus
hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus.description: Specifies the current status of this reaction entry: invalid - Specifies the reaction entry status is uncertain. overThreshold - Specifies the reaction entry has met the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType and the threshold value. belowThreshold - Specifies the reaction entry has disobeyed the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType and the threshold value.

hh3cNqaReactRowStatus.name: hh3cNqaReactRowStatus
hh3cNqaReactRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
hh3cNqaReactRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the hh3cNqaReactionTable. Creation of an entry in this table results in a new set of reaction configurations which take effect immediately. Deletion of an entry in this table results in corresponding reaction configurations are being deleted and stop taking effect.

hh3cNqaReactCheckedNum.name: hh3cNqaReactCheckedNum
hh3cNqaReactCheckedNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are monitored.

hh3cNqaReactThresholdNum.name: hh3cNqaReactThresholdNum
hh3cNqaReactThresholdNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are over threshold.

hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable.name: hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable
hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable.description: A table of NQA test monitoring notification and reaction configuration definitions. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding pingCtlEntry is deleted.

hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionEntry.name: hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionEntry
hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable. The first two index elements identify the pingCtlEntry that a hh3cNqaReactItemIndex belongs to. The third index element identifies an entry in the hh3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The forth index element selects a single reaction.

hh3cNqaStatReactOwnerIndex.name: hh3cNqaStatReactOwnerIndex
hh3cNqaStatReactOwnerIndex.description: The first index of hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlOwnerIndex in pingCtlTable.

hh3cNqaStatReactTestName.name: hh3cNqaStatReactTestName
hh3cNqaStatReactTestName.description: The second index of hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlTestName in pingCtlTable.

hh3cNqaStatReactIndex.name: hh3cNqaStatReactIndex
hh3cNqaStatReactIndex.description: The third index of hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable. An entry in this table is created when the statistics result of a NQA probe is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning hh3cNqaStatResIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

hh3cNqaStatReactItemIndex.name: hh3cNqaStatReactItemIndex
hh3cNqaStatReactItemIndex.description: The forth index of hh3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it definitely identifies one of the reaction configurations for a test

hh3cNqaStatReactCheckedNum.name: hh3cNqaStatReactCheckedNum
hh3cNqaStatReactCheckedNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are monitored.

hh3cNqaStatReactThresholdNum.name: hh3cNqaStatReactThresholdNum
hh3cNqaStatReactThresholdNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are over threshold.

hh3cNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold.name: hh3cNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold
hh3cNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. Probe time(equals to RTT for some type of tests) is not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. 2. The probe time is accumulatively not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum. 3. The probe time is consecutively in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is not hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold.name: hh3cNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold
hh3cNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average NQA round-trip-time (RTT) of jitter packets is not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. 2. The RTT of jitter packets is accumulatively not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaProbeFailure.name: hh3cNqaProbeFailure
hh3cNqaProbeFailure.description: It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the probe test accumulatively failed for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test while the value of hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is 'accumulative'. 2. When the probe test consecutively failed for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum in one test while the value of hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is 'consecutive'. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is not hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaJitterPacketLoss.name: hh3cNqaJitterPacketLoss
hh3cNqaJitterPacketLoss.description: It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the jitter packets accumulatively lost for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test while the value of hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is 'accumulative'. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaJitterSDOverThreshold.name: hh3cNqaJitterSDOverThreshold
hh3cNqaJitterSDOverThreshold.description: The SD means the jitter values from source to destination. It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average of SD in one jitter test is not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit and the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'average' type. 2. The average of SD in one jitter test is accumulatively not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum and the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'accumulative' type. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaJitterDSOverThreshold.name: hh3cNqaJitterDSOverThreshold
hh3cNqaJitterDSOverThreshold.description: The DS means the jitter values from destination to source. It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average of DS in one jitter test is not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit and the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'average' type. 2. The average of DS in one jitter test is accumulatively not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hh3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum and the hh3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'accumulative' type. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter.

hh3cNqaICPIFOverThreshold.name: hh3cNqaICPIFOverThreshold
hh3cNqaICPIFOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the ICPIF value in one jitter test is not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger', pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter and hh3cNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.

hh3cNqaMOSOverThreshold.name: hh3cNqaMOSOverThreshold
hh3cNqaMOSOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hh3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the MOS value in one jitter test is not in the range hh3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hh3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. This notification is valid only when hh3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger', pingCtlType of the test is hh3cNqajitter and hh3cNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.
